Class
Description
AddLifeBehavior
The power up behavior for the life fruit
App
App creates a stage and a scene.
BossEnemy
One type of enemy.
BossProgressController
This is the controller which handles the boss life progress bar.
BossProjectile
The BossProjectile class handles the specificities with the projectile being shot from the boss.
It also can hurt a hero.
Bubble
The Bubble class handles everything with the Hero's special ability, named the bubble.
It begins at the hero, and grows covering the whole screen.
Once it collides with an enemy, that enemy is bubbled.
It is a dynamic object.
BubbleBehavior
The power up behavior for the bubble fruit
BubbleFruit
The type of fruit which has the bubble power up for the hero.
BubbleTest
 
CeilingUnit
The CeilingUnit class creates ceiling units to be used for the world.
It's a static object which has the same image as wall and floor.
A ceiling unit is a unit shaped like a square that is treated as a ceiling, with collision on all four sides.
The ceiling collides with any kind of game object.
Even if a game object is on top of a ceiling, the game object will be pushed down.
DifficultyState
This is the state of different difficulty of the game chosen by player.
DynamicObject
DynamicObject is the game object like projectiles, hero, enemies, bubble and fruit.
EasyState
Easy difficulty.
Enemy
An Enemy is a non-controllable DynamicObject that kills the Hero whenever it or its projectile comes in contact.
Enemies are able to be bubbled and free themselves from these bubbles after 5 seconds.
Enemies change direction at random intervals, when hitting a wall, and when hitting Hero's shield.
Enemies jump at random intervals as well.
3 types of enemies.
EnemyProjectile
The EnemyProjectile class handles the specificities with the projectile being shot from a shootEnemy or the boss.
It also can only hurt a hero.
EnemyProjectileTest
 
FloorUnit
The FloorUnit class creates floor units to be used for the world.
A floor unit is a unit shaped like a square that is treated as a floor replace by imageview which has the same image as wall,
with collision on the top, left, and right sides.
The floor collides with any kind of dynamic object.
When an enemy is bubbled, the enemy will still be stopped by a floor unit above it.
Fruit
The Fruit class handles how the fruit is created and interacts with the hero.
The normal fruit is created after a bubble containing an enemy is popped.
The other three are the power up fruit which will show only one of the three in each level.
Four types of fruits one normal fruit, one bubble fruit, one invincible fruit,and one life fruit.
It's a dynamic object.
GameController
Game controller handles all game's operations:
updating positions, checking for collisions, handling switching levels,
draw the map according to different difficulty of the game, the text shown on the
screen and removing objects.
GameObject
GameObjects are the objects on the controller.Game controller screen.
Every GameObject has a velocity, acceleration, position, direction.
It can be divided into two subclasses which are staticObject and DynamicObject since
some of the object we don't need to handle the velocity and the collision.
GameObjectFactory
GameObjectFactory is for generating different object according to different signs on the maps.
This class implements the Factory method design pattern.
GameView
GameView class handles the screen of the game.
Initialize the game view with a background choose by the player
HardState
Hard difficulty.
Hero
A Hero is a DynamicObject that is controllable by the player.
HeroProjectile
The HeroProjectile class handles the specificities with the projectile being shot from a hero.
After the collision with enemy, enemy will become bubble.
HeroState
The state of the hero.
HighScore
HighScore is for storing the player name and the total point they get.
HighScoreController
HighController class is for the control of the high score board(Game Over)
The only difference between a highscore board and a win screen is high score board show when you lose
Win screen is when you win but also shows the history five highest records.
HighScoreTest
 
InfoScoreController
InfoController class is for the control of the Info page
InvincibleBehavior
The power up behavior for the invincible fruit
InvincibleFruit
The type of fruit which has the invincible power up for the hero.
InvincibleState
A state of the hero which won't die when colliding with enemy or enemy projectile.
LifeFruit
The type of fruit which adds one life of the hero.
Main
Main class for launching.
MediumState
Medium difficulty.
NormalBehavior
The powerup behavior for the normal fruit.
NormalFruit
The type of fruit which has no power up behavior but only points according to different fruit which falls down from different enemies.
NormalState
Normal state can shoot can shield and will die after collision with enemies and projectiles.
NotShootEnemy
The enemy that cannot shoot.
Observer
Observer interface for observer pattern
PauseController
PauseController class is for pause screen during the game
PlayerInputController
This is the controller which handles the player input screen.
Two actions of two buttons are handled.
PowerUpBehavior
The power behavior for different types of fruit
Projectile
Projectile shoot from shootEnemy or boss enemy or hero.
Also a dynamic object. 3 types heroProjectile, BossProjectile, and enemyProjectile.
ScoreTextObserver
The observer for updating the temporary display score text on the screen.
SettingController
SettingController class is for the setting event control
ShieldState
Shield state cannot shoot won't die after collision with enemies and projectiles.
ShootEnemy
The enemy that can shoot
SoundEffect
SoundEffect handles the game's SFX.
SoundEffect.Volume
Volumn of the sound mute low medium and high
startScreenController
startScreenController class is for the control of the start screen
startScreenControllerTest
 
StaticObject
Static object is wall unit ceiling unit and floor unit which all of them cannot move.
StunState
Stun state cannot move.
Subject
Subject interface for observer pattern
TotalScoreObserver
The observer for updating the total score in the top right corner of the screen.
WallUnit
The WallUnit class creates wall units to be used for the world.
A wall unit is an unit shaped like a square which replace by the image view wall with different colors,
with collision on all four sides.
The wall collides with any kind of dynamic object.
WinController
WinController class is for the control of the player win screen
